ssages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></section><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="858a098e-c75a-4ffc-889e-ca986482194a" data-testid="conversation-turn-4" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="dd551424-c770-4c70-ab59-d54ff313ba75" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="175">Got it — you want a <strong data-start="20" data-end="51">strong, ready-to-use prompt</strong> to paste into <strong data-start="66" data-end="88">Amazon Q (VS Code)</strong> so it generates a working project using a pretrained model for your <strong data-start="157" data-end="169">RxAssist</strong> idea.</p>
<p data-start="177" data-end="242">Here’s a <strong data-start="186" data-end="216">clean, professional prompt</strong> you can directly paste 👇</p>
<hr data-start="244" data-end="247">
<h2 data-section-id="si15dv" data-start="249" data-end="269">✅ Amazon Q Prompt</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="271" data-end="1880"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are a senior AI + full-stack developer.</span><br><br><span>Build a complete working project called "RxAssist: AI System for Decoding Doctor Prescriptions".</span><br><br><span>Objective:</span><br><span>Create an application that takes an image of a handwritten doctor prescription as input and outputs only the extracted and cleaned text in a readable format.</span><br><br><span>Requirements:</span><br><br><span>1. Use a pretrained model for handwriting recognition:</span><br><span>   - Prefer TrOCR (Microsoft), EasyOCR, or Tesseract OCR.</span><br><span>   - The model must work well for handwritten medical prescriptions.</span><br><br><span>2. Backend:</span><br><span>   - Use Python (FastAPI or Flask).</span><br><span>   - Create an API endpoint:</span><br><span>     POST /predict</span><br><span>     Input: image file (jpg/png)</span><br><span>     Output: extracted text only (no extra explanation).</span><br><br><span>3. Processing pipeline:</span><br><span>   - Accept image input</span><br><span>   - Preprocess image (grayscale, noise removal, thresholding)</span><br><span>   - Run OCR model</span><br><span>   - Clean the output (remove noise, fix spacing, basic formatting)</span><br><br><span>4. Output format:</span><br><span>   - Return ONLY the final extracted prescription text</span><br><span>   - No JSON explanation, no metadata</span><br><br><span>5. Frontend (simple):</span><br><span>   - Use HTML + CSS + JS (or React if preferred)</span><br><span>   - Upload image</span><br><span>   - Display extracted text</span><br><br><span>6. Project structure:</span><br><span>   - Separate folders: backend/, frontend/</span><br><span>   - Include requirements.txt</span><br><span>   - Include clear run instructions</span><br><br><span>7. Extra:</span><br><span>   - Make the code runnable in VS Code</span><br><span>   - Add sample test image</span><br><span>   - Ensure minimal dependencies</span><br><br><span>8. Do NOT:</span><br><span>   - Train a model from scratch</span><br><span>   - Add unnecessary features like login or database</span><br><br><span>Deliver:</span><br><span>- Full code (backend + frontend)</span><br><span>- Installation steps</span><br><span>- How to run locally</span><br><br><span>Focus on simplicity, accuracy, and working output.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1882" data-end="1885">
<h2 data-section-id="1elee99" data-start="1887" data-end="1931">🔥 Pro Tip (important for your hackathon)</h2>
<p data-start="1932" data-end="1986">After Amazon Q generates this, you can extend it with:</p>
<ul data-start="1988" data-end="2077">
<li data-section-id="1wvavj8" data-start="1988" data-end="2015">
<p data-start="1990" data-end="2015">Medicine name detection</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="13150nc" data-start="2016" data-end="2053">
<p data-start="2018" data-end="2053">Dosage extraction (e.g., “1-0-1”)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1r0eh7k" data-start="2054" data-end="2077">
<p data-start="2056" data-end="2077">Notification system</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2079" data-end="2082">
<p data-start="2084" data-end="2330" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you want, I can next:<br>
