<h2 data-section-id="1vm2k8i" data-start="142" data-end="177">✅ Amazon Q Prompt (Backend Only)</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="179" data-end="1659"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are a senior AI/ML engineer.</span><br><br><span>Build a backend-only project called "RxAssist: Prescription OCR API".</span><br><br><span>Objective:</span><br><span>Create a Python API that accepts an image of a handwritten doctor prescription and returns ONLY the extracted clean text using a pretrained model.</span><br><br><span>Requirements:</span><br><br><span>1. Use pretrained OCR model:</span><br><span>   - Prefer EasyOCR or TrOCR (HuggingFace)</span><br><span>   - Do NOT train any model from scratch</span><br><br><span>2. Backend:</span><br><span>   - Use FastAPI (preferred) or Flask</span><br><span>   - Create endpoint:</span><br><span>     POST /predict</span><br><span>     Input: image file (jpg/png)</span><br><span>     Output: plain text (ONLY extracted prescription text)</span><br><br><span>3. Pipeline:</span><br><span>   - Load image</span><br><span>   - Preprocess (convert to grayscale, resize, denoise, threshold)</span><br><span>   - Run OCR model</span><br><span>   - Post-process text:</span><br><span>       * remove noise/symbols</span><br><span>       * fix spacing</span><br><span>       * join broken words</span><br><span>   - Return final cleaned text</span><br><br><span>4. Output format:</span><br><span>   - Return ONLY raw text</span><br><span>   - No JSON keys, no explanation</span><br><br><span>5. Code structure:</span><br><span>   - main.py (API)</span><br><span>   - ocr_utils.py (OCR + preprocessing)</span><br><span>   - requirements.txt</span><br><br><span>6. Performance:</span><br><span>   - Load model once at startup (not per request)</span><br><span>   - Optimize for CPU usage</span><br><br><span>7. Include:</span><br><span>   - Sample test image path</span><br><span>   - Example curl command to test API</span><br><br><span>8. Keep it simple:</span><br><span>   - No frontend</span><br><span>   - No database</span><br><span>   - No authentication</span><br><br><span>Deliver:</span><br><span>- Complete working code</span><br><span>- Steps to install dependencies</span><br><span>- Steps to run server in VS Code</span><br><span>- Example API call</span><br><br><span>Goal:</span><br><span>When I upload a prescription image, I should get ONLY the readable text output.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
