argin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="user" data-message-id="d5759bfb-57f9-445e-8e37-b85e42777d60" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden items-end rtl:items-start"><div class="user-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%)"><div class="whitespace-pre-wrap">The system follows a modular layered architecture, integrating voice processing, NLP, email management, scheduling, and document intelligence into a unified AI-powered administrative platform.
The Voice Processing Module converts speech input into text using a speech-to-text engine, enabling hands-free interaction for administrators.
The Text Processing and NLP Modules perform normalization, tokenization, named entity recognition, and sentiment analysis to extract actionable insights from user input.
The Core Service Modules handle email automation (priority detection and summarization), calendar synchronization with conflict detection, and intelligent document search and summarization.
A centralized API security layer ensures secure communication between frontend and backend services through encrypted API requests.
The Authentication and Role-Based Access Control module protects user data and restricts system functionality based on user roles (Principal, HOD, Admin).

give it in this format with bullet points
</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></section><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="421269b7-3712-440a-9673-acd1911abc43" data-testid="conversation-turn-12" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="421269b7-3712-440a-9673-acd1911abc43" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="85">Here is your <strong data-start="13" data-end="82">Proposed Model written in the same structured bullet-point format</strong> 👇</p>
<hr data-start="87" data-end="90">
<p data-start="92" data-end="274">The system follows a <strong data-start="113" data-end="145">modular layered architecture</strong>, integrating image processing, OCR, NLP, and notification services into a unified AI-powered prescription assistance platform.</p>
<ul data-start="276" data-end="2001">
<li data-section-id="1ugq7bx" data-start="276" data-end="445">
<p data-start="278" data-end="445">The <strong data-start="282" data-end="310">Image Acquisition Module</strong> captures or accepts uploaded images of handwritten doctor prescriptions, supporting low-quality inputs common in rural environments.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="139o2it" data-start="447" data-end="623">
<p data-start="449" data-end="623">The <strong data-start="453" data-end="483">Image Preprocessing Module</strong> enhances the input image by applying grayscale conversion, noise removal, contrast enhancement, and thresholding to improve OCR accuracy.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="mw86dy" data-start="625" data-end="794">
<p data-start="627" data-end="794">The <strong data-start="631" data-end="677">OCR (Optical Character Recognition) Module</strong> uses pretrained models such as TrOCR or EasyOCR to convert handwritten prescription content into raw digital text.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="16630px" data-start="796" data-end="1020">
<p data-start="798" data-end="1020">The <strong data-start="802" data-end="836">Text Processing and NLP Module</strong> performs text cleaning, normalization, and structuring by removing noise, correcting spacing, and identifying key entities such as medicine names, dosage patterns, and instructions.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1tjeo0v" data-start="1022" data-end="1250">
<p data-start="1024" data-end="1250">The <strong data-start="1028" data-end="1071">AI Interpretation Module (LLM with RAG)</strong> refines the extracted information by correcting medical terms, simplifying instructions into user-friendly language, and enhancing understanding using a medical knowledge base.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1saudh3" data-start="1252" data-end="1375">
<p data-start="1254" data-end="1375">The <strong data-start="1258" data-end="1281">Core Service Module</strong> generates clear prescription outputs and creates structured medication schedules for users.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="emul4w" data-start="1377" data-end="1528">
<p data-start="1379" data-end="1528">The <strong data-start="1383" data-end="1406">Notification Module</strong> provides timely reminders for medication intake through integrations such as SMS, Gmail API, or Google Calendar alerts.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1xj2wfp" data-start="1530" data-end="1697">
<p data-start="1532" data-end="1697">The <strong data-start="1536" data-end="1568">Database Module (PostgreSQL)</strong> securely stores extracted prescriptions, user data, medication schedules, and reminder logs for future reference and tracking.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="59d8ng" data-start="1699" data-end="1824">
<p data-start="1701" data-end="1824">A centralized <strong data-start="1715" data-end="1737">API Security Layer</strong> ensures secure communication between system components using encrypted API requests.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1g3yuy5" data-start="1826" data-end="2001">
<p data-start="1828" data-end="2001">The <strong data-start="1832" data-end="1887">Authentication and Role-Based Access Control Module</strong> protects user data and restricts system functionality based on roles (e.g., Admin, Healthcare Worker, Patient).</p>
</li>
</ul>
