<hr data-start="67" data-end="70">
<h2 data-section-id="170onjw" data-start="72" data-end="94">✅ Model Explanation</h2>
<p data-start="96" data-end="264">The proposed model is an <strong data-start="121" data-end="168">AI-based prescription interpretation system</strong> that converts handwritten medical prescriptions into clear and understandable text for users.</p>
<p data-start="266" data-end="469">The process begins by capturing or uploading an image of the prescription, which is then enhanced using image preprocessing techniques such as grayscale conversion and noise removal to improve clarity.</p>
<p data-start="471" data-end="794">A pretrained <strong data-start="484" data-end="513">OCR model (TrOCR/EasyOCR)</strong> is used to extract handwritten text from the image. Since raw OCR output may contain errors or irregular formatting, a <strong data-start="633" data-end="659">text processing module</strong> cleans and structures the extracted data by correcting spacing and identifying key elements like medicine names and dosage patterns.</p>
<p data-start="796" data-end="997">The refined text is further processed using an <strong data-start="843" data-end="859">LLM with RAG</strong>, which simplifies complex medical instructions into easy-to-understand language and improves accuracy by referencing medical knowledge.</p>
<p data-start="999" data-end="1190">Finally, the system generates a <strong data-start="1031" data-end="1063">readable prescription output</strong> and optionally creates medication schedules with reminders, ensuring that users take the correct medicine at the right time.</p>
<hr data-start="1192" data-end="1195">
<h3 data-section-id="1jlm3or" data-start="1197" data-end="1239">🎯 One-Line Version (for quick answer)</h3>
