<hr data-start="178" data-end="181">
<h1 data-section-id="4mgmzj" data-start="183" data-end="200">✅ Research Gaps</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="1dm2w7a" data-start="202" data-end="261">📄 Paper 1 (IEEE – Handwritten Prescription Recognition)</h2>
<ul data-start="262" data-end="564">
<li data-section-id="1ej3lqr" data-start="262" data-end="360">
<p data-start="264" data-end="360">Most models focus only on <strong data-start="290" data-end="309">text extraction</strong>, not on <strong data-start="318" data-end="358">user understanding or simplification</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1380dkj" data-start="361" data-end="430">
<p data-start="363" data-end="430">Limited handling of <strong data-start="383" data-end="428">poor-quality or noisy prescription images</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1xtukwr" data-start="431" data-end="496">
<p data-start="433" data-end="496">Lack of support for <strong data-start="453" data-end="494">regional languages and rural contexts</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="t9xaan" data-start="497" data-end="564">
<p data-start="499" data-end="564">No integration with <strong data-start="519" data-end="564">reminder or healthcare assistance systems</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="566" data-end="569">
<h2 data-section-id="12tsezy" data-start="571" data-end="622">📄 Paper 2 (HAL – Document/OCR &amp; NLP Processing)</h2>
<ul data-start="623" data-end="920">
<li data-section-id="amcbsd" data-start="623" data-end="704">
<p data-start="625" data-end="704">Focuses mainly on <strong data-start="643" data-end="676">technical OCR/NLP performance</strong>, not real-world usability</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="lqmda2" data-start="705" data-end="784">
<p data-start="707" data-end="784">Does not address <strong data-start="724" data-end="755">medical-specific challenges</strong> like dosage interpretation</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1s7drxt" data-start="785" data-end="861">
<p data-start="787" data-end="861">Limited ability to <strong data-start="806" data-end="859">structure extracted data into actionable insights</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1lu6yjr" data-start="862" data-end="920">
<p data-start="864" data-end="920">No support for <strong data-start="879" data-end="920">end-user interaction or accessibility</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="922" data-end="925">
<h2 data-section-id="1xef7z4" data-start="927" data-end="989">📄 Paper 3 (IEEE – Medicine Extraction using Deep Learning)</h2>
<ul data-start="990" data-end="1341">
<li data-section-id="3obbvc" data-start="990" data-end="1076">
<p data-start="992" data-end="1076">Primarily targets <strong data-start="1010" data-end="1038">medicine name extraction</strong>, ignoring full prescription context</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="yy6yoz" data-start="1077" data-end="1187">
<p data-start="1079" data-end="1187">Does not fully extract <strong data-start="1102" data-end="1147">dosage, timing, and instructions together</strong> <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 37px;"><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.18199?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.18199?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]! select-none" style="max-width: 37px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">arXiv</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="rc3leq" data-start="1188" data-end="1265">
<p data-start="1190" data-end="1265">Requires <strong data-start="1199" data-end="1218">custom datasets</strong>, making it hard to generalize across regions</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="wv5ibm" data-start="1266" data-end="1341">
<p data-start="1268" data-end="1341">Lacks integration with <strong data-start="1291" data-end="1341">real-time applications (APIs, reminders, etc.)</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1343" data-end="1346">
<h2 data-section-id="b4lk53" data-start="1348" data-end="1408">📄 Paper 4 (Springer – Medical Informatics / NLP Systems)</h2>
<ul data-start="1409" data-end="1680">
<li data-section-id="1e3xc61" data-start="1409" data-end="1485">
<p data-start="1411" data-end="1485">Focuses on <strong data-start="1422" data-end="1452">structured medical records</strong>, not handwritten prescriptions</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1bb6jjq" data-start="1486" data-end="1543">
<p data-start="1488" data-end="1543">Limited support for <strong data-start="1508" data-end="1541">unstructured handwritten data</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ovz4nz" data-start="1544" data-end="1618">
<p data-start="1546" data-end="1618">Does not simplify outputs into <strong data-start="1577" data-end="1616">user-friendly language for patients</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="fdcc32" data-start="1619" data-end="1680">
<p data-start="1621" data-end="1680">No integration with <strong data-start="1641" data-end="1680">AI assistants or automation systems</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1682" data-end="1685">
<h2 data-section-id="wz114f" data-start="1687" data-end="1722">📄 Common Gaps Across All Papers</h2>
<ul data-start="1723" data-end="2064">
<li data-section-id="1otkyz2" data-start="1723" data-end="1799">
<p data-start="1725" data-end="1799">❌ No <strong data-start="1730" data-end="1751">end-to-end system</strong> (OCR → NLP → User-friendly output → Reminder)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="18i1n3u" data-start="1800" data-end="1856">
<p data-start="1802" data-end="1856">❌ Lack of focus on <strong data-start="1821" data-end="1854">rural users and accessibility</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1tw6q03" data-start="1857" data-end="1921">
<p data-start="1859" data-end="1921">❌ Minimal use of <strong data-start="1876" data-end="1919">LLMs for simplification and explanation</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="zx0h1w" data-start="1922" data-end="1989">
<p data-start="1924" data-end="1989">❌ No <strong data-start="1929" data-end="1987">real-time notification or medication adherence support</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1j60266" data-start="1990" data-end="2064">
<p data-start="1992" data-end="2064">❌ Limited handling of <strong data-start="2014" data-end="2062">multi-language and low-resource environments</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2066" data-end="2069">
<h2 data-section-id="vhdstb" data-start="2071" data-end="2121">🎯 Final Gap Statement (Use this in PPT/report)</h2>
<p data-start="2122" data-end="2340">👉 <em data-start="2125" data-end="2340">“Existing systems focus mainly on text extraction and lack an end-to-end solution that converts handwritten prescriptions into simple, actionable instructions with real-time reminders, especially for rural users.”</em></p>
<hr data-start="2342" data-end="2345">
<p data-start="2347" data-end="2578">If you want, I can next:<br>
✅ Map these gaps → <strong data-start="2391" data-end="2444">your proposed solution (very important for marks)</strong><br data-start="2444" data-end="2447">
✅ Or convert this into a <strong data-start="2472" data-end="2523">perfect “Problem vs Existing vs Proposed” table</strong><br data-start="2523" data-end="2526">
✅ Or make it <strong data-start="2539" data-end="2575">1-slide PPT ready (clean visual)</strong> 🚀</p>
