<h2 data-section-id="1w5vdjw" data-start="157" data-end="201">✅ Amazon Q Prompt (API-Based OCR Backend)</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="203" data-end="2101"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are a senior Python backend developer.</span><br><br><span>Build a complete backend project called "RxAssist API" using FastAPI that extracts text from handwritten prescription images using ONLY external OCR APIs (no local ML models).</span><br><br><span>Objective:</span><br><span>Create a FastAPI server that accepts an image and returns ONLY the extracted text using Google Vision API.</span><br><br><span>Requirements:</span><br><br><span>1. Tech Stack:</span><br><span>   - Python</span><br><span>   - FastAPI</span><br><span>   - Requests library</span><br><span>   - Google Vision API (using API key)</span><br><br><span>2. API Endpoint:</span><br><span>   - POST /predict</span><br><span>   - Input: image file (jpg/png)</span><br><span>   - Output: plain text only (no JSON keys, no explanation)</span><br><br><span>3. Functionality:</span><br><span>   - Accept uploaded image using FastAPI</span><br><span>   - Convert image to base64</span><br><span>   - Send request to Google Vision API:</span><br><span>       Endpoint: https://vision.googleapis.com/v1/images:annotate</span><br><span>       Feature: TEXT_DETECTION</span><br><span>   - Extract text from response:</span><br><span>       responses[0].fullTextAnnotation.text</span><br><span>   - Clean output:</span><br><span>       * remove extra spaces</span><br><span>       * remove unnecessary symbols</span><br><span>       * format into readable lines</span><br><br><span>4. Code Structure:</span><br><span>   - main.py (FastAPI app)</span><br><span>   - utils.py (OCR + cleaning logic)</span><br><span>   - requirements.txt</span><br><br><span>5. Important Constraints:</span><br><span>   - DO NOT use any local OCR models (no EasyOCR, no Tesseract, no TrOCR)</span><br><span>   - Use ONLY API key-based OCR</span><br><span>   - Load API key from environment variable (not hardcoded)</span><br><br><span>6. Additional Features:</span><br><span>   - Add error handling if no text is detected</span><br><span>   - Handle invalid image uploads</span><br><span>   - Keep response simple and clean</span><br><br><span>7. Provide:</span><br><span>   - Full working code</span><br><span>   - requirements.txt</span><br><span>   - Step-by-step setup instructions</span><br><span>   - Example curl command to test API</span><br><span>   - .env usage for API key</span><br><br><span>8. Example Output:</span><br><span>   Input: prescription image  </span><br><span>   Output:</span><br><span>   Paracetamol 500mg</span><br><span>   1 tablet morning and night after food</span><br><br><span>Goal:</span><br><span>The system should be simple, fast, and fully working in VS Code using an API key, without any machine learning model setup.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
