-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="3cb0991c-be70-48d9-9dae-70f83474de76" data-testid="conversation-turn-42" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="3cb0991c-be70-48d9-9dae-70f83474de76" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="184">Got you 👍 — you’re asking for <strong data-start="31" data-end="104">real projects/papers where they actually trained models with datasets</strong> (not just APIs). That’s exactly what you should cite for strong academic value.</p>
<p data-start="186" data-end="255">Here are <strong data-start="195" data-end="252">solid examples + explanation + what dataset they used</strong> 👇</p>
<hr data-start="257" data-end="260">
<h1 data-section-id="km5n9g" data-start="262" data-end="307">✅ 📚 Projects with Trained Models + Dataset</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="1tfgy48" data-start="309" data-end="371">1️⃣ Handwritten Prescription Recognition using CNN + BiLSTM</h2>
<ul data-start="372" data-end="658">
<li data-section-id="1qh3sf3" data-start="372" data-end="404">
<p data-start="374" data-end="404"><strong data-start="374" data-end="389">Model Used:</strong> CNN + BiLSTM</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="rzxmiz" data-start="405" data-end="519">
<p data-start="407" data-end="421"><strong data-start="407" data-end="419">Dataset:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="424" data-end="519">
<li data-section-id="2p6flj" data-start="424" data-end="471">
<p data-start="426" data-end="471">Custom dataset of handwritten prescriptions</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="9bozks" data-start="474" data-end="519">
<p data-start="476" data-end="519">Includes medicine names + dosage patterns</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="4y24oy" data-start="520" data-end="614">
<p data-start="522" data-end="540"><strong data-start="522" data-end="540">What they did:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="543" data-end="614">
<li data-section-id="om05ny" data-start="543" data-end="579">
<p data-start="545" data-end="579">Image → CNN (feature extraction)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1dxb3p9" data-start="582" data-end="614">
<p data-start="584" data-end="614">BiLSTM → sequence prediction</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="73qzb0" data-start="615" data-end="658">
<p data-start="617" data-end="658"><strong data-start="617" data-end="628">Output:</strong> Extracted prescription text</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="660" data-end="749">👉 ✔ Strong for: handwriting recognition<br data-start="700" data-end="703">
👉 ❌ Limitation: needs large labeled dataset</p>
<hr data-start="751" data-end="754">
<h2 data-section-id="khmr19" data-start="756" data-end="806">2️⃣ TrOCR-Based Prescription Recognition System</h2>
<ul data-start="807" data-end="1050">
<li data-section-id="5dhsrq" data-start="807" data-end="850">
<p data-start="809" data-end="850"><strong data-start="809" data-end="824">Model Used:</strong> TrOCR (Transformer OCR)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="qspjb7" data-start="851" data-end="956">
<p data-start="853" data-end="867"><strong data-start="853" data-end="865">Dataset:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="870" data-end="956">
<li data-section-id="10v8vzn" data-start="870" data-end="907">
<p data-start="872" data-end="907">IAM Handwriting Dataset (general)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="91gf3k" data-start="910" data-end="956">
<p data-start="912" data-end="956">Fine-tuned on medical prescription samples</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1cc6059" data-start="958" data-end="1050">
<p data-start="960" data-end="978"><strong data-start="960" data-end="978">What they did:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="981" data-end="1050">
<li data-section-id="wu1nte" data-start="981" data-end="1012">
<p data-start="983" data-end="1012">Used pretrained transformer</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1xa8aou" data-start="1015" data-end="1050">
<p data-start="1017" data-end="1050">Fine-tuned on prescription data</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1052" data-end="1113">👉 ✔ High accuracy (~90%+)<br data-start="1078" data-end="1081">
👉 ❌ Needs GPU + training time</p>
<hr data-start="1115" data-end="1118">
<h2 data-section-id="1a99h5n" data-start="1120" data-end="1167">3️⃣ Medical Text Extraction using BERT + OCR</h2>
<ul data-start="1168" data-end="1364">
<li data-section-id="1gtrr7d" data-start="1168" data-end="1239">
<p data-start="1170" data-end="1187"><strong data-start="1170" data-end="1185">Model Used:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1190" data-end="1239">
<li data-section-id="1a7gxs7" data-start="1190" data-end="1209">
<p data-start="1192" data-end="1209">OCR (Tesseract)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1hqbghw" data-start="1212" data-end="1239">
<p data-start="1214" data-end="1239">BERT for classification</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1wzylpc" data-start="1241" data-end="1364">
<p data-start="1243" data-end="1255"><strong data-start="1243" data-end="1255">Dataset:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1258" data-end="1364">
<li data-section-id="j4ces" data-start="1258" data-end="1292">
<p data-start="1260" data-end="1292">Annotated prescription dataset</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1s30bp0" data-start="1295" data-end="1364">
<p data-start="1297" data-end="1314">Labeled entities:</p>
<ul data-start="1319" data-end="1364">
<li data-section-id="sfq1os" data-start="1319" data-end="1331">
<p data-start="1321" data-end="1331">Medicine</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ihb1hv" data-start="1336" data-end="1346">
<p data-start="1338" data-end="1346">Dosage</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="19jzoy4" data-start="1351" data-end="1364">
<p data-start="1353" data-end="1364">Frequency</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1366" data-end="1427">👉 ✔ Extracts structured info<br data-start="1395" data-end="1398">
👉 ❌ Depends on OCR quality</p>
<hr data-start="1429" data-end="1432">
<h2 data-section-id="1d30uht" data-start="1434" data-end="1484">4️⃣ YOLO + OCR Prescription Digitization System</h2>
<ul data-start="1485" data-end="1662">
<li data-section-id="17jeb4a" data-start="1485" data-end="1542">
<p data-start="1487" data-end="1502"><strong data-start="1487" data-end="1502">Model Used:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1505" data-end="1542">
<li data-section-id="bnbs12" data-start="1505" data-end="1532">
<p data-start="1507" data-end="1532">YOLO (object detection)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="16tvdg6" data-start="1535" data-end="1542">
<p data-start="1537" data-end="1542">OCR</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1b2ifdd" data-start="1544" data-end="1662">
<p data-start="1546" data-end="1558"><strong data-start="1546" data-end="1558">Dataset:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1561" data-end="1662">
<li data-section-id="1g02rle" data-start="1561" data-end="1594">
<p data-start="1563" data-end="1594">Annotated prescription images</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1rw4n5v" data-start="1597" data-end="1662">
<p data-start="1599" data-end="1618">Bounding boxes for:</p>
<ul data-start="1623" data-end="1662">
<li data-section-id="1jipn6g" data-start="1623" data-end="1641">
<p data-start="1625" data-end="1641">Medicine names</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1w6iosj" data-start="1646" data-end="1662">
<p data-start="1648" data-end="1662">Instructions</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1664" data-end="1730">👉 ✔ Detects regions + improves accuracy<br data-start="1704" data-end="1707">
👉 ❌ Complex pipeline</p>
<hr data-start="1732" data-end="1735">
<h2 data-section-id="swoj2m" data-start="1737" data-end="1790">5️⃣ MIRAGE (Multimodal Prescription Understanding)</h2>
<ul data-start="1791" data-end="1894">
<li data-section-id="1sul45s" data-start="1791" data-end="1833">
<p data-start="1793" data-end="1808"><strong data-start="1793" data-end="1808">Model Used:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1811" data-end="1833">
<li data-section-id="1pn4a79" data-start="1811" data-end="1833">
<p data-start="1813" data-end="1833">Vision + LLM model</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1i3jzem" data-start="1834" data-end="1894">
<p data-start="1836" data-end="1848"><strong data-start="1836" data-end="1848">Dataset:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1851" data-end="1894">
<li data-section-id="1vzbwc1" data-start="1851" data-end="1894">
<p data-start="1853" data-end="1894">Multimodal dataset (image + text pairs)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1896" data-end="1968">👉 ✔ Advanced system (state-of-the-art)<br data-start="1935" data-end="1938">
👉 ❌ Heavy + not lightweight</p>
<hr data-start="1970" data-end="1973">
<h1 data-section-id="3srnrl" data-start="1975" data-end="2020">✅ 📊 Common Datasets Used in These Projects</h1>
<p data-start="2022" data-end="2060">You can mention this in your report 👇</p>
<ul data-start="2062" data-end="2262">
<li data-section-id="ehy57s" data-start="2062" data-end="2115">
<p data-start="2064" data-end="2115"><strong data-start="2064" data-end="2091">IAM Handwriting Dataset</strong> (general handwriting)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1e1yrmj" data-start="2116" data-end="2151">
<p data-start="2118" data-end="2151"><strong data-start="2118" data-end="2149">MIMIC-III (medical records)</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="11arauj" data-start="2152" data-end="2209">
<p data-start="2154" data-end="2209"><strong data-start="2154" data-end="2186">Custom Prescription Datasets</strong> (collected manually)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="bjwg8n" data-start="2210" data-end="2262">
<p data-start="2212" data-end="2262"><strong data-start="2212" data-end="2234">Synthetic datasets</strong> (generated prescriptions)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2264" data-end="2267">
<h1 data-section-id="1j1anwc" data-start="2269" data-end="2299">❌ Problems in These Projects</h1>
<ul data-start="2301" data-end="2567">
<li data-section-id="ukidh" data-start="2301" data-end="2357">
<p data-start="2303" data-end="2357">Require <strong data-start="2311" data-end="2337">large labeled datasets</strong> (hard to collect)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="jvu018" data-start="2358" data-end="2411">
<p data-start="2360" data-end="2411">Training is <strong data-start="2372" data-end="2409">time-consuming and resource-heavy</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1eemc7g" data-start="2412" data-end="2457">
<p data-start="2414" data-end="2457">Not suitable for <strong data-start="2431" data-end="2455">real-time deployment</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1mxnjbf" data-start="2458" data-end="2510">
<p data-start="2460" data-end="2510">Poor performance on <strong data-start="2480" data-end="2508">messy real prescriptions</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="gx38qp" data-start="2511" data-end="2567">
<p data-start="2513" data-end="2567">No focus on <strong data-start="2525" data-end="2565">user understanding (only extraction)</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2569" data-end="2572">
<h1 data-section-id="h9qael" data-start="2574" data-end="2608">⚠️ Research Gap from These Works</h1>
<p data-start="2610" data-end="2825">👉 <em data-start="2613" data-end="2825">“Existing systems rely heavily on trained models and large datasets for prescription recognition, but they lack lightweight, real-time solutions and fail to provide user-friendly interpretation and assistance.”</em></p>
<hr data-start="2827" data-end="2830">
<h1 data-section-id="13nilmq" data-start="2832" data-end="2864">🎯 How You Can Explain in Viva</h1>
<p data-start="2866" data-end="3112">👉 <em data-start="2869" data-end="3112">“Some systems use trained models like CNN, BiLSTM, and Transformers with datasets such as IAM or custom prescription datasets. However, these require heavy training, so our approach uses API-based OCR for faster and scalable implementation.”</em></p>
<hr data-start="3114" data-end="3117">
<h1 data-section-id="2ji317" data-start="3119" data-end="3155">🔥 Important Insight (VERY USEFUL)</h1>
<p data-start="3157" data-end="3189">You now have <strong data-start="3170" data-end="3188">two approaches</strong>:</p>
<h3 data-section-id="j16zua" data-start="3191" data-end="3222">🧠 Research Papers Approach</h3>
<ul data-start="3223" data-end="3272">
<li data-section-id="1tjhuaq" data-start="3223" data-end="3252">
