<h1 data-section-id="1q0c4me" data-start="140" data-end="188">✅ Gemini Prompt (Training CNN on Your Dataset)</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="190" data-end="1791"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are an expert AI/ML engineer.</span><br><br><span>I have a dataset of handwritten characters for medical prescription recognition. The dataset is organized in folders where each folder name represents the label (e.g., A, B, C, 0, 1, etc.), and contains corresponding images.</span><br><br><span>Build a complete Google Colab training pipeline using CNN with the following requirements:</span><br><br><span>1. Dataset Handling:</span><br><span>   - Load dataset from a given path (Google Drive or local upload)</span><br><span>   - Automatically detect class labels from folder names</span><br><span>   - Split dataset into training (80%) and validation (20%)</span><br><br><span>2. Preprocessing:</span><br><span>   - Convert images to grayscale</span><br><span>   - Resize images to 64x64</span><br><span>   - Normalize pixel values (0–1)</span><br><span>   - Apply optional augmentation (rotation, zoom)</span><br><br><span>3. Model:</span><br><span>   - Build a CNN model using TensorFlow/Keras</span><br><span>   - Include:</span><br><span>       * Conv2D + MaxPooling layers</span><br><span>       * Dropout layers to avoid overfitting</span><br><span>       * Dense output layer with softmax</span><br><br><span>4. Training:</span><br><span>   - Train for 10–15 epochs</span><br><span>   - Show accuracy and loss graphs</span><br><span>   - Use callbacks (EarlyStopping)</span><br><br><span>5. Evaluation:</span><br><span>   - Print validation accuracy</span><br><span>   - Show confusion matrix</span><br><br><span>6. Save Model:</span><br><span>   - Save trained model as model.h5</span><br><span>   - Save label encoder/classes</span><br><br><span>7. Prediction:</span><br><span>   - Add function to predict a single image</span><br><br><span>8. Code Style:</span><br><span>   - Fully runnable in Google Colab</span><br><span>   - Use clear comments</span><br><span>   - Use GPU if available</span><br><br><span>9. Input:</span><br><span>   - I will provide dataset path like:</span><br><span>     /content/drive/MyDrive/dataset/</span><br><br><span>Goal:</span><br><span>Train a working CNN model that can recognize handwritten characters from prescription images and save it as a reusable .h5 file.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
