<hr data-start="220" data-end="223">
<h1 data-section-id="taauze" data-start="225" data-end="265">✅ 🧠 FULL GEMINI PROMPT (COPY &amp; PASTE)</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="267" data-end="3516"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are an expert AI/ML engineer.</span><br><br><span>Build a complete end-to-end handwritten prescription recognition system in Google Colab using TensorFlow, Keras, and OpenCV.</span><br><br><span>I will provide a dataset of handwritten characters (similar to EMNIST or folder-based dataset).</span><br><br><span>The system must include TRAINING, TESTING, and FULL PIPELINE.</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>1. DATASET HANDLING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Load dataset from Google Drive path:</span><br><span>  /content/drive/MyDrive/dataset/</span><br><span>- Dataset may be:</span><br><span>  a) CSV format (like EMNIST)</span><br><span>  OR</span><br><span>  b) Folder-based (each folder = label)</span><br><br><span>- Automatically detect labels</span><br><span>- Split into:</span><br><span>  - 80% training</span><br><span>  - 20% validation</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>2. PREPROCESSING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Convert images to grayscale</span><br><span>- Resize to 28x28</span><br><span>- Normalize pixel values (0–1)</span><br><span>- Reshape to (28,28,1)</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>3. MODEL (CNN)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Build a multi-layer CNN model:</span><br><br><span>- Conv2D → BatchNormalization → ReLU → MaxPooling</span><br><span>- Dropout</span><br><span>- Repeat multiple Conv blocks</span><br><span>- Flatten</span><br><span>- Dense layer</span><br><span>- Dropout</span><br><span>- Output layer with softmax</span><br><br><span>Output classes = number of labels</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>4. TRAINING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Compile model:</span><br><span>    optimizer = Adam</span><br><span>    loss = sparse_categorical_crossentropy</span><br><span>    metrics = accuracy</span><br><br><span>- Train:</span><br><span>    epochs = 15–20</span><br><span>    batch_size = 64</span><br><span>    validation_split = 0.2</span><br><br><span>- Show:</span><br><span>    training accuracy</span><br><span>    validation accuracy</span><br><span>    loss graph</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>5. SAVE MODEL</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Save trained model as:</span><br><span>    model.h5</span><br><span>- Save class labels</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>6. TESTING (SINGLE CHARACTER)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Load model</span><br><span>- Take test image</span><br><span>- Preprocess same as training</span><br><span>- Predict class</span><br><span>- Convert to actual character label</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>7. FULL PRESCRIPTION PIPELINE</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Build full system using OpenCV:</span><br><br><span>Step 1: Load prescription image</span><br><span>Step 2: Resize (300x300)</span><br><span>Step 3: Convert to grayscale</span><br><span>Step 4: Apply image processing:</span><br><span>    - Median blur</span><br><span>    - absdiff</span><br><span>    - normalize</span><br><span>    - morphologyEx</span><br><span>    - CLAHE</span><br><span>Step 5: Apply thresholding (binary image)</span><br><br><span>Step 6: Contour detection:</span><br><span>    - Find bounding boxes of characters</span><br><br><span>Step 7: Character segmentation:</span><br><span>    - Crop each character</span><br><span>    - Sort by x and y coordinates</span><br><br><span>Step 8: Prediction:</span><br><span>    - Resize each char to 28x28</span><br><span>    - Pass to CNN model</span><br><span>    - Get predicted character</span><br><br><span>Step 9: Combine characters:</span><br><span>    - Form words from sequence</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>8. POST-PROCESSING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Fix common OCR errors:</span><br><span>    e.g., "crocim" → "crocin"</span><br><span>- Use simple dictionary matching for medicine names</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>9. OUTPUT</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Print final extracted text from prescription</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>10. EXTRA</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Add comments in code</span><br><span>- Ensure it runs in Colab</span><br><span>- Use GPU if available</span><br><span>- Make code clean and modular</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>GOAL:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Build a complete working system:</span><br><span>Image → Preprocessing → Character Detection → CNN → Word Output</span><br><br><span>The output should be readable prescription text.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
