<hr data-start="86" data-end="89">
<h1 data-section-id="3nf1nk" data-start="91" data-end="143"><span role="text">✅ When <strong data-start="100" data-end="143">Training Accuracy &lt; Validation Accuracy</strong></span></h1>
<p data-start="145" data-end="173">👉 This situation is called:</p>
<h1 data-section-id="ofwpsy" data-start="175" data-end="223"><span role="text">🟡 <strong data-start="180" data-end="223">Underfitting (or Regularization Effect)</strong></span></h1>
<hr data-start="225" data-end="228">
<h1 data-section-id="kakesb" data-start="230" data-end="248">🧠 What It Means</h1>
<p data-start="250" data-end="264">👉 Your model:</p>
<ul data-start="265" data-end="355">
<li data-section-id="1q1na7c" data-start="265" data-end="306">
<p data-start="267" data-end="306">Has <strong data-start="271" data-end="306">not fully learned training data</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="t0t5e3" data-start="307" data-end="355">
<p data-start="309" data-end="355">But performs <strong data-start="322" data-end="355">slightly better on validation</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="357" data-end="360">
<h1 data-section-id="wknvcp" data-start="362" data-end="374">📊 Example</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="376" data-end="437"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Training Accuracy = 80%</span><br><span>Validation Accuracy = 85%</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="439" data-end="442">
<h1 data-section-id="14yypp9" data-start="444" data-end="465">🤔 Why This Happens</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="17r880z" data-start="467" data-end="499">✅ 1. Dropout / Regularization</h2>
<ul data-start="500" data-end="576">
<li data-section-id="im4von" data-start="500" data-end="550">
<p data-start="502" data-end="550">During training → neurons are randomly dropped</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="avrwa9" data-start="551" data-end="576">
<p data-start="553" data-end="576">Makes training harder</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="578" data-end="603">👉 But during validation:</p>
<ul data-start="604" data-end="644">
<li data-section-id="1lkorxq" data-start="604" data-end="618">
<p data-start="606" data-end="618">No dropout</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="195ss5x" data-start="619" data-end="644">
<p data-start="621" data-end="644">Model performs better</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="646" data-end="649">
<h2 data-section-id="o6v6k0" data-start="651" data-end="676">✅ 2. Data Augmentation</h2>
<ul data-start="677" data-end="758">
<li data-section-id="kytpb1" data-start="677" data-end="727">
<p data-start="679" data-end="727">Training data is <strong data-start="696" data-end="725">harder (distorted images)</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="9abx0s" data-start="728" data-end="758">
<p data-start="730" data-end="758">Validation data is <strong data-start="749" data-end="758">clean</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="760" data-end="763">
<h2 data-section-id="5480c" data-start="765" data-end="796">✅ 3. Model Not Fully Trained</h2>
<ul data-start="797" data-end="840">
<li data-section-id="c3acp6" data-start="797" data-end="815">
<p data-start="799" data-end="815">Too few epochs</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1fk5pr1" data-start="816" data-end="840">
<p data-start="818" data-end="840">Model still learning</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="842" data-end="845">
<h1 data-section-id="1iwyy5r" data-start="847" data-end="872">🎯 Is This Good or Bad?</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="o46zep" data-start="874" data-end="913">🟢 Slightly higher validation → GOOD</h2>
<p data-start="914" data-end="953">👉 Means model is <strong data-start="932" data-end="953">generalizing well</strong></p>
<hr data-start="955" data-end="958">
<h2 data-section-id="1p2m33o" data-start="960" data-end="998">🔴 Much higher validation → PROBLEM</h2>
<p data-start="999" data-end="1010">👉 Example:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1011" data-end="1051"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Train = 60%</span><br><span>Validation = 90%</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1053" data-end="1094">👉 Something wrong (data leakage / issue)</p>
<hr data-start="1096" data-end="1099">
<h1 data-section-id="14kyqev" data-start="1101" data-end="1124">🔧 What You Should Do</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="5t14si" data-start="1126" data-end="1152">If difference is small:</h2>
<p data-start="1153" data-end="1184">👉 ✔ Leave it — model is fine</p>
<hr data-start="1186" data-end="1189">
<h2 data-section-id="179i00" data-start="1191" data-end="1217">If difference is large:</h2>
<p data-start="1218" data-end="1225">👉 Try:</p>
<ul data-start="1226" data-end="1287">
<li data-section-id="3cu97y" data-start="1226" data-end="1245">
<p data-start="1228" data-end="1245">Increase epochs</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="b5841o" data-start="1246" data-end="1263">
<p data-start="1248" data-end="1263">Check dataset</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1307ij8" data-start="1264" data-end="1287">
<p data-start="1266" data-end="1287">Reduce augmentation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1289" data-end="1292">
<h1 data-section-id="rv9s5f" data-start="1294" data-end="1309">🧪 Ideal Case</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1311" data-end="1344"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Training ≈ Validation</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1346" data-end="1354">Example:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1355" data-end="1395"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Train = 85%</span><br><span>Validation = 87%</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1397" data-end="1409">👉 ✔ Perfect</p>
<hr data-start="1411" data-end="1414">
<h1 data-section-id="y077be" data-start="1416" data-end="1432">🎤 Viva Answer</h1>
<p data-start="1434" data-end="1651">👉 <em data-start="1437" data-end="1651">“If validation accuracy is higher than training accuracy, it may be due to regularization techniques like dropout or data augmentation, and it generally indicates good generalization unless the gap is too large.”</em></p>
<hr data-start="1653" data-end="1656">
<h1 data-section-id="1w2vhb2" data-start="1658" data-end="1679">🎯 One-Line Summary</h1>
<p data-start="1681" data-end="1734">👉 <em data-start="1684" data-end="1734">Training &lt; Validation = Normal (if gap is small)</em></p>
<hr data-start="1736" data-end="1739">
