👉 <strong data-start="109" data-end="179">proper segmentation + multiple characters detection (not just “B”)</strong></p>
<hr data-start="181" data-end="184">
<h1 data-section-id="17xdbex" data-start="186" data-end="231">✅ 🧠 GEMINI PROMPT (FIX SEGMENTATION ISSUE)</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="233" data-end="3052"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are an expert in Computer Vision and OCR systems.</span><br><br><span>I have a trained CNN model (model.h5) for handwritten character recognition (28x28 grayscale). However, when I input a full prescription image, the system detects only one contour and predicts a single character (like "B").</span><br><br><span>Fix this issue by building a robust character segmentation pipeline using OpenCV.</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>OBJECTIVE:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Input: Full prescription image</span><br><span>Output:</span><br><span>- Detect multiple characters (not one)</span><br><span>- Draw bounding boxes around each character</span><br><span>- Count number of detected contours</span><br><span>- Extract each character separately</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>1. IMAGE LOADING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Load image using OpenCV</span><br><span>- Resize to reasonable size (300–600 px)</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>2. PREPROCESSING (IMPORTANT)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Convert to grayscale</span><br><span>- Apply Gaussian Blur</span><br><span>- Improve contrast if needed</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>3. THRESHOLDING (CRITICAL)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Use BOTH methods and compare:</span><br><br><span>Method 1:</span><br><span>- Adaptive Threshold (Gaussian)</span><br><span>- cv2.adaptiveThreshold()</span><br><br><span>Method 2:</span><br><span>- Otsu Threshold</span><br><span>- cv2.threshold()</span><br><br><span>Choose the one that produces better separation.</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>4. MORPHOLOGICAL OPERATIONS</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Apply opening (remove noise)</span><br><span>- Apply dilation (separate characters if merged)</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>5. CONTOUR DETECTION</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Use cv2.findContours()</span><br><span>- Detect all contours</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>6. FILTERING (VERY IMPORTANT)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Remove noise using:</span><br><span>    if width &lt; threshold OR height &lt; threshold → ignore</span><br><span>- Keep only meaningful character regions</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>7. SORTING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Sort contours:</span><br><span>    left-to-right</span><br><span>    top-to-bottom (line-wise)</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>8. VISUALIZATION</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Draw bounding boxes on image</span><br><span>- Display number of contours detected</span><br><span>- Show segmented character images</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>9. DEBUG OUTPUT</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Print:</span><br><span>- Number of contours before filtering</span><br><span>- Number after filtering</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>10. EXPECTED RESULT</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Instead of 1 contour → detect MANY characters (20–100)</span><br><span>- Each character boxed separately</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>IMPORTANT:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- DO NOT run prediction yet</span><br><span>- Focus ONLY on segmentation</span><br><span>- Fix the issue where full image is treated as one object</span><br><span>- Make output visually clear</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>GOAL:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Correct segmentation so that each character can later be passed to the CNN model.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
