bberish output) by adding <strong data-start="120" data-end="175">post-processing + word correction + better grouping</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="178" data-end="181">
<h1 data-section-id="w55ij4" data-start="183" data-end="239">✅ 🧠 GEMINI PROMPT (FIX GIBBERISH OUTPUT → CLEAN TEXT)</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="241" data-end="3080"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-cohbnghc.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>You are an expert AI/ML engineer specializing in OCR and NLP.</span><br><br><span>I have already:</span><br><span>- Trained a CNN model (model.h5) on EMNIST (character-level recognition)</span><br><span>- Built segmentation using OpenCV</span><br><span>- Extracted characters and predicted them</span><br><br><span>Problem:</span><br><span>The output text is gibberish (incorrect words like "LeI E", "f EFk").</span><br><br><span>Fix this by improving the pipeline and making the output readable.</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>OBJECTIVE:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Input: Prescription image</span><br><span>Output: Clean, readable medicine text</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>1. KEEP EXISTING PIPELINE</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Image preprocessing (grayscale, thresholding)</span><br><span>- Contour detection</span><br><span>- Character extraction</span><br><span>- CNN prediction</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>2. IMPROVE CHARACTER FILTERING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Remove noise:</span><br><span>    Ignore contours with very small width/height</span><br><span>- Ignore predictions with low confidence (&lt; 0.5)</span><br><span>- Remove isolated random characters</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>3. IMPROVE SORTING (VERY IMPORTANT)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Group characters into lines:</span><br><span>    Sort by Y-axis (top to bottom)</span><br><span>- Within each line:</span><br><span>    Sort by X-axis (left to right)</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>4. WORD FORMATION</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Combine characters into words based on spacing:</span><br><span>    If gap between characters &gt; threshold → new word</span><br><span>- Combine words into lines</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>5. TEXT CLEANING</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Convert all text to lowercase</span><br><span>- Remove repeated or meaningless characters</span><br><span>- Remove symbols or noise</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>6. MEDICINE DICTIONARY MATCHING (KEY STEP)</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Use fuzzy matching to correct words:</span><br><br><span>Example dictionary:</span><br><span>["augmentin", "enzoflam", "pantoprazole", "hexigel", "paracetamol"]</span><br><br><span>Use Python:</span><br><span>- difflib.get_close_matches()</span><br><span>OR</span><br><span>- fuzzywuzzy</span><br><br><span>Example:</span><br><span>"crocim" → "crocin"</span><br><span>"paracitamol" → "paracetamol"</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>7. FINAL OUTPUT FORMAT</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Print clean result like:</span><br><br><span>Augmentin 625mg</span><br><span>Enzoflam</span><br><span>PanD 40mg</span><br><span>Hexigel</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>8. DEBUG OUTPUT</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Print:</span><br><span>- Raw predicted text</span><br><span>- Cleaned text</span><br><span>- Corrected text</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>9. IMPROVEMENT LOGIC</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- If word not matching dictionary → keep original</span><br><span>- Use best match only if similarity &gt; 60%</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>IMPORTANT:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>- Do NOT change the CNN model</span><br><span>- Focus on improving output readability</span><br><span>- Assume model predictions are noisy</span><br><span>- Use post-processing to fix errors</span><br><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>GOAL:</span><br><span>-------------------------------</span><br><span>Transform noisy character predictions into readable prescription text using intelligent correction.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
